  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7107 sitting just below the GEX flip at 7112 and massive negative gamma walls at 7115/7110, dealers are currently in amplifying mode and likely buying this dip aggressively to hedge short gamma positions. The -2.3% 1-minute move suggests we're seeing the acceleration effects of negative gamma, but the proximity to the flip means any bounce back above 7112 will shift dealers into stabilizing mode where they'll sell rallies. Key levels to watch are the 7112 flip strike for regime change and the 7115 max negative gamma strike where dealer buying pressure should be most intense.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile whipsaw action around 7110 with dealers providing buying support but capping any rallies above 7112.",
